Cell.Text: <<Shared>> This is a straight forward assignment. We need you to assassinate the rebel field commander. It will disorient them and make them less eager.
<<Shared>> We need to cut the head off the Legion here. I need you to slay the Imperial field legate.

Node.Caption: CWMission05Brief: Tell me more about the assassination.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> It's less than honorable, but you need to find a way to penetrate the defenses and take him out. Be careful. Don't make it a one way trip.
<<Shared>> It's not honorable, but we need this - for the good of Skyrim. Slip in there and kill him, then get out. Don't make this a one way trip.
<<Shared>> This won't be easy, but that's why I'm sending you. Think you can handle it?
<<Shared>> No point in honey-coating. This won't be easy. But that's why I'm sending you. You got the grit to get this done?
<<Shared>> Don't take too long figuring it out, I've got a war to run here.
<<Shared>> I see, make it quick, or do you have better things to do than fight for the people of Skyrim?

Node.Caption: CWMission05AcceptNo: I'm not sure. I need to think about it.

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> I knew I could count on you, soldier.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Good luck out there.
[S] G|<<Shared>> We do this for the good of Skyrim and her people. Never forget that.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Make me proud.
[S] G|<<Shared>> May the gods keep you.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Stay sharp out there.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Good. Make it it happen, soldier.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Show the rebels the futility of their cause.
[S] G|<<Shared>> As long as the rebels are willing to die fighting the Empire, we must be willing to kill them.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Peace may yet return to Skyrim. But until then, we fight with our all.
